Brilliant.

1560
01:29:49,960 --> 01:29:51,950
I didn't know that.

1561
01:29:51,950 --> 01:29:53,940
I liked him.

1562
01:29:53,940 --> 01:29:56,430
I liked him a lot.

1563
01:30:10,110 --> 01:30:13,820
-Did Lyle say what the
 argument with Robert was about?

1564
01:30:13,820 --> 01:30:16,770
-Robert overheard me telling
 you I didn't like him.

1565
01:30:16,770 --> 01:30:17,270
-Oh.

1566
01:30:25,160 --> 01:30:27,420
-Do you really think I'm mean?

1567
01:30:27,420 --> 01:30:29,400
-You're a fine person, Marian.

1568
01:30:35,340 --> 01:30:39,060
What did Lyle really say to you?

1569
01:30:39,060 --> 01:30:41,660
-It's about me.

1570
01:30:41,660 --> 01:30:42,160
Hey.

1571
01:30:44,930 --> 01:30:45,430
Oh.

1572
01:30:45,430 --> 01:30:48,240
Did Mommy upset you, too?

1573
01:30:48,240 --> 01:30:51,670
There Mommy.

1574
01:30:51,670 --> 01:30:52,580
There Mommy.

1575
01:31:19,900 --> 01:31:22,220
-Anything interesting
 in the "Times".

1576
01:31:22,220 --> 01:31:25,860
-One laugh after another.

1577
01:31:25,860 --> 01:31:28,340
-Why is it that you look
 the best in the peace

1578
01:31:28,340 --> 01:31:31,350
and quiet that follows
 a violent storm?

1579
01:31:31,350 --> 01:31:34,850
-Well, I am something
 of a season campaigner.

1580
01:31:34,850 --> 01:31:37,060
What's up?

1581
01:31:37,060 --> 01:31:38,140
-My schedule.

1582
01:31:38,140 --> 01:31:41,910
We're going to
 Toronto on Thursday.

1583
01:31:41,910 --> 01:31:44,620
-Oh, well, will you
 have any spare time?

1584
01:31:44,620 --> 01:31:47,640
I mean, you could stay
 up here a few days.

1585
01:31:47,640 --> 01:31:49,680
Thierry, too, of
 course, if you'd like.

1586
01:31:49,680 --> 01:31:53,580
-The only place I'll be
 seeing Thierry is at the set.

1587
01:31:53,580 --> 01:31:54,550
-Oh.

1588
01:31:54,550 --> 01:31:57,910
I'm sorry.

1589
01:31:57,910 --> 01:32:01,770
-No, you're not.

1590
01:32:01,770 --> 01:32:07,660
He was just another way of
 punishing you, and hurting

1591
01:32:07,660 --> 01:32:09,500
myself.

1592
01:32:09,500 --> 01:32:11,830
And I think it's
 about time I stopped

1593
01:32:11,830 --> 01:32:15,620
doing both of those things.

1594
01:32:15,620 --> 01:32:16,770
-That would make me very happy.

1595
01:32:19,560 --> 01:32:26,620
Listen, um, I didn't misbehave
 too badly last night, did I?

1596
01:32:26,620 --> 01:32:29,020
-No, half the time
 you were charming.

1597
01:32:29,020 --> 01:32:32,370
-And the other half?

1598
01:32:32,370 --> 01:32:34,320
-You thought you were charming.

1599
01:32:44,100 --> 01:32:46,500
You loved Atorian
 very much, didn't you?

1600
01:32:50,000 --> 01:32:51,560
-As much as you
 loved your father.

1601
01:32:56,420 --> 01:32:59,530
Well, they're still alive
 in our dreams, aren't they?

1602
01:33:02,980 --> 01:33:03,480
-Yeah.

1603
01:33:36,140 --> 01:33:37,840
-It's better going
 back to the city

1604
01:33:37,840 --> 01:33:40,910
than leaving it don't you think?

1605
01:33:40,910 --> 01:33:43,860
Lyle?

1606
01:33:43,860 --> 01:33:47,790
It's comforting traveling in
 the same direction as the river.

1607
01:33:47,790 --> 01:33:48,290
-Hmm.

1608
01:34:00,420 --> 01:34:02,810
-I do feel awful about
 what happened with Robert.

1609
01:34:05,580 --> 01:34:10,030
When the two of you came here
 to stay, you were both so happy.

1610
01:34:10,030 --> 01:34:13,000
I wasn't nice to him.

1611
01:34:13,000 --> 01:34:13,500
-No.

1612
01:34:21,420 --> 01:34:23,430
It wasn't about Robert.

1613
01:34:23,430 --> 01:34:24,600
It was about Tony.

1614
01:34:24,600 --> 01:34:25,570
-I know.

1615
01:34:31,920 --> 01:34:35,330
-Mourning should sooth the
 objects, not the subjects.

1616
01:34:39,240 --> 01:34:40,970
-And I don't mourn Tony well.

1617
01:34:44,420 --> 01:34:55,290
-Neither do I. Will
 you invite Robert back?

1618
01:34:58,050 --> 01:34:59,350
Do you want me to call him?

1619
01:34:59,350 --> 01:35:00,530
-I will.

1620
01:35:00,530 --> 01:35:01,030
-OK.

1621
01:35:08,150 --> 01:35:09,880
-That's us.

1622
01:35:09,880 --> 01:35:10,620
Well, me.

1623
01:35:17,630 --> 01:35:20,540
-Are we still friends?

1624
01:35:20,540 --> 01:35:22,380
-Of course, we are.

1625
01:35:31,290 --> 01:35:31,790
-OK.

1626
01:36:07,920 --> 01:36:08,420
-Lyle.

1627
01:36:12,120 --> 01:36:16,980
In your life, love never
 gets expressed directly.

1628
01:36:16,980 --> 01:36:19,460
You get in touch
 with your emotions,

1629
01:36:19,460 --> 01:36:22,370
and then you run away from them.

1630
01:36:22,370 --> 01:36:25,150
-But you know I love you.

1631
01:36:25,150 --> 01:36:28,030
-It shouldn't require so
 much effort on my part.

1632
01:36:30,980 --> 01:36:36,170
Promise me things
 will be different.

1633
01:36:36,170 --> 01:36:39,150
After.

1634
01:36:39,150 --> 01:36:41,630
-I don't want there
 to be an after.

1635
01:36:47,080 --> 01:36:47,580
-Promise.

1636
01:37:00,970 --> 01:37:05,430
-There are things you lose
 you don't ever get back.

1637
01:37:05,430 --> 01:37:08,280
You can never have them again
 except in the smudging carbon

1638
01:37:08,280 --> 01:37:11,240
copy of memory.

1639
01:37:11,240 --> 01:37:15,520
There are things that seem
 irreconcilable that you

1640
01:37:15,520 --> 01:37:19,490
must find a way
 to reconcile with.

1641
01:37:19,490 --> 01:37:22,770
The simple passage of days
 dulls the sharpness of the pain,

1642
01:37:22,770 --> 01:37:26,470
but never quite wears it out.

1643
01:37:26,470 --> 01:37:28,010
And it doesn't get
 washed away in time.

1644
01:37:28,010 --> 01:37:31,790
It becomes a cold hard
 lump of something.

1645
01:37:31,790 --> 01:37:33,210
And a loseable souvenir.

1646
01:37:45,930 --> 01:37:49,230
Tony told me once.

1647
01:37:49,230 --> 01:37:51,980
There's no future in
 holding on to the past.

